        "id": 255504,
        "name": "Jeremy",
        "username": "jeremysee",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/jeremysee/{size}/49574_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-11-14T00:35:07.358Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Having seen these screenshots of the old &amp; new systray icons side by side:<br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/a/0/a0efa64d67dafe55c9226d5717c1bdd8b454fa82.png\" alt=\"signal3\" data-base62-sha1=\"mXHQdsDHLKEq4lkP3MrLJCEw0cq\" width=\"431\" height=\"48\"><br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/6/76c42dd7a379b2a06ef2c80c175f4e3006bf515e.png\" alt=\"signal5\" data-base62-sha1=\"gWEEv2jki5mdH5Vqaktdmxx1rcy\" width=\"454\" height=\"44\"></p>\n<p>…I now realize the main source of the problem is the new icon. And then that problem is severely compounded when there’s an unread badge on top.</p>\n<p>A tray icon this illegible on a black background is unacceptable, guys. Many many people have black taskbars.</p>\n<p>Either change the icon to something like this (a square / rounded-square shape would be less obscured by bagdes):<br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/d/7/d7cdadd4b0bb20b61c1c1ed8194157b93d235afa.png\" alt=\"signal4\" data-base62-sha1=\"uN5jVzu7w3462dUU1o3yR5HExe2\" width=\"48\" height=\"48\"></p>\n<p>Or if you want to stick with monochrome, the tray icon needs to be either user-selectable or dark mode aware.</p>",
